{"TopicId":218416,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Docking Visualization","CreatedByName":"Nicrose","CreatedById":224410,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-14T17:17:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nicrose","CreatedById":224410,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-14T17:17:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it just me or does anyone else miss that docking window visualization? I thought it was very helpful and intuitive when docking and using the controls for monopropellant thrusters. Is it permanently gone or just not added yet?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Here\u0027s a picture of the UI I\u0027m referencing\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Docking_lin.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002238.17\u0022 height=\u002292\u0022 width=\u0022241\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/2/2e/Docking_lin.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-17T18:32:35Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2023 06:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 17\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Nicrose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-15T10:59:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe what now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoCDoC","CreatedById":229939,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-16T01:57:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m with \u0022The Aziz\u0022 Nicrose can you show a example picture?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lyneira","CreatedById":149515,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T08:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe they\u0027re referring to the docking port alignment indicator mod for KSP 1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002277044\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2137499552\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/40423-181-docking-port-alignment-indicator-version-685-updated-121419/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KUAR","CreatedById":229322,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T11:32:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224302529\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689355024\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224410\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nicrose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/14/2023 at 6:17 PM, Nicrose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it just me or does anyone else miss that docking window visualization? I thought it was very helpful and intuitive when docking and using the controls for monopropellant thrusters. Is it permanently gone or just not added yet?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m with the others above, I reckon you installed a mod and got so used to it you forgot it wasn\u0027t stock!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know the one,it is good and definitely a valuable feature\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T13:05:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689593528\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229322\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KUAR\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, KUAR said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI reckon you installed a mod and got so used to it you forgot it wasn\u0027t stock!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow come? I always used navball markers for docking. I never needed a mod for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nicrose","CreatedById":224410,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T18:22:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689593528\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229322\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KUAR\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, KUAR said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m with the others above, I reckon you installed a mod and got so used to it you forgot it wasn\u0027t stock!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know the one,it is good and definitely a valuable feature\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be it, it\u0027s been a long time however tbh I don\u0027t really remember getting too into mods. I found an image from a youtube video of what I\u0027m describing though! I coulda sworn this was stock but I\u0027m second guessing now with how many people don\u0027t know about it lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Docking_lin.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002238.17\u0022 height=\u002292\u0022 width=\u0022241\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/2/2e/Docking_lin.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689472640\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoCDoC\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/15/2023 at 8:57 PM, DoCDoC said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m with \u0022The Aziz\u0022 Nicrose can you show a example picture?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust posted one in my last comment \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689583886\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149515\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lyneira\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Lyneira said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe they\u0027re referring to the docking port alignment indicator mod for KSP 1?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002277044\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9442420234\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/40423-181-docking-port-alignment-indicator-version-685-updated-121419/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter checking out that mod, I can confirm it isn\u0027t that mod. It may have been another one I suppose but definitely did not use that one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303448\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689599111\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow come? I always used navball markers for docking. I never needed a mod for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell in KSP 2 I am forced to do that but idk, I just enjoyed the other perspective and the 2D representation of position resonated with my brain better \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EEDIT: Just looked on the KSP Wiki and found the page talking about it. It turns out it was in fact vanilla KSP!\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Docking\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Docking\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/File:Docking_lin.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/File:Docking_lin.png\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-17T18:35:21Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2023 06:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 17\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Nicrose\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KUAR","CreatedById":229322,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T21:02:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689618176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224410\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nicrose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nicrose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be it, it\u0027s been a long time however tbh I don\u0027t really remember getting too into mods. I found an image from a youtube video of what I\u0027m describing though! I coulda sworn this was stock but I\u0027m second guessing now with how many people don\u0027t know about it lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/2/2e/Docking_lin.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Docking_lin.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002238.17\u0022 height=\u002292\u0022 width=\u0022241\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/2/2e/Docking_lin.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust posted one in my last comment \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter checking out that mod, I can confirm it isn\u0027t that mod. It may have been another one I suppose but definitely did not use that one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell in KSP 2 I am forced to do that but idk, I just enjoyed the other perspective and the 2D representation of position resonated with my brain better \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EEDIT: Just looked on the KSP Wiki and found the page talking about it. It turns out it was in fact vanilla KSP!\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Docking\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Docking\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/File:Docking_lin.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/File:Docking_lin.png\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh yes, now I do remember that. I just never used it really, found it awkward and preferred the modded one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-17T23:38:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689618176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224410\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nicrose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Nicrose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut idk, I just enjoyed the other perspective and the 2D representation of position resonated with my brain better\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResonated with my brain better... We are indeed a spoiled generation. I remember times when astronauts were real men, and they\u0027ve been doing docking by eyeballing it. One in the command module, pressing buttons, while the other floted in the vacuum of space, holding breath, waving directions...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough*... aaanyway, I guess similar gizmo will find its way into the game eventually. Many of these QOL features are not present atm...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngryBaer","CreatedById":227014,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-18T02:44:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I would love is if this could be modified to come with a camera view under that docking mode square from the POV of the docking node.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nicrose","CreatedById":224410,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-18T22:27:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689648275\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AngryBaer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, AngryBaer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I would love is if this could be modified to come with a camera view under that docking mode square from the POV of the docking node.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would actually be awesome!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-19T10:51:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any lights on docking ports? That would be a nice addition when you\u0027re on the dark side... I used to add Mk illuminator above each one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nicrose","CreatedById":224410,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-19T18:09:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224303965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221689763909\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any lights on docking ports? That would be a nice addition when you\u0027re on the dark side... I used to add Mk illuminator above each one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think due to performance reasons they will probably skip that since you can put your own lights where you need them but that\u0027s just speculation of course\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}